item.title: [ENTESB-3189] Unable to install 2 patches on Fuse without access to Internet
item.description:

item.summary: Unable to install 2 patches on Fuse without access to Internet

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.

comments.comment: Attached dummy patches that can be used for reproducing the problem.
It seems that the same problem is present even with access to internet.

Roman Jakubco - I can't reproduce this on my machine: after doing the two patch:add commands, the new bundle versions are sitting in the system folder as expected and the subsequent patch:install's work fine for me.

What OS are you testing this on? Is there any specific configuration in your Maven settings.xml file? Could you retry this and check if the redhat-620119 and redhat-620120 bundles are available in the system folder after doing the patch:add commands?

I am using ubuntu right now, but it seems to be problem with java. I tried it again with oracle-jdk-7 and it works fine, but the oracle-jdk-8 doesn't. Patching with oracle-jdk-8 produces the same error as described in the issue. I was testing it on build 118

The problem seems to be related to the implementation of the mvn URL that is being used: there are two implementations around in JBoss Fuse, one provided by Pax URL and one by the Fabric8 project. If the latter ends up being selected, that will cause this exception. It is also possible to reproduce the issue with the first patch, by stopping the Pax URL Aether bundle.

https://github.com/jboss-fuse/fuse/pull/176 fixes the issue by removing the fabric-maven-proxy feature from the default feature set for JBoss Fuse. Also, I added a sensible default configuration, in case the user later installs this features himself before applying patches.

customfieldvalues.customfieldvalue:
1. start Fuse without access to Internet
  2. patch:add file:/karaf-119.zip
  3. patch:add file:/karaf-120.zip
  4. patch:install karaf-patch-119
  5. patch:install karaf-patch-120
